Restaurants are no longer treating lunchtime delivery as an afterthought. With online-ordering apps proliferating and many customers cutting down on eating out for lunch, the industry-- from fast-food chains to upscale restaurateurs-- is looking for ways to bring food to patrons without compromising their eating experience. Wendy's Co. (WEN) recently signed up with delivery service DoorDash Inc. to offer delivery in parts of Ohio and Texas, with plans to expand nationally within...

















